 this is achieved by diversion of blood primarily from skeletal muscle tissue and by increasing the volume of blood pumped forward by the heart each minute. The flow of oxygen and blood to the brain is extremely tightly regulated by the circulatory system and does not drop after a meal,[17] and is not a cause of post-meal sleepiness.[18]"},{"pid":"97edd0e2d69b62665d0a626c3aea8d993acd2cf7","tid":730104,"uid":29929,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"b3dce71c71e052866dcb458aee6e1fd3c824f850","tid":730104,"uid":52942,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"quote":{"pid":"594adfbce282aaa7e06c4a8750519f6e6481953f","tid":730104,"uid":29929,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"dba00b09229c5b3fcfa76f78455a9ab6f57c57ad","tid":730104,"uid":2896,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-07-05T08:14:25.000Z","msg":"咁你點解釋飯後做運動影響消化？"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-07-05T08:18:14.000Z","msg":"Redistribution of blood<br />\n<br />\n你咁講做運動 血集中係肌肉到啦 但blood flow to brain kept constant"},"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2018-07-05T08:21:06.000Z","msg":"屌，我求其google 一段都屌打你條假膠<br />\n<br />\n康奈爾大學營養與心理學教授David Levitsky解釋，「當食物進入胃部並激活胃腸道時，身體會『通知』我們要消化剛吃過的食物，血液從大腦和肌肉轉移到胃和腸裏。當血液離開大腦時，頭腦會變得疲憊，容易打呵欠。"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-07-05T08:23:03.000Z","msg":"佢其實9up都得<br />\n有無paper?"},{"pid":"5b2c749ea47101433753885075fb9c013bf11363","tid":730104,"uid":44569,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-07-05T08:24:25.000Z","msg":"Food coma, or postprandial somnolence, is a condition that can occur after eating a large meal. It is usually described as a feeling of extreme fatigue or lethargy that can last for several hours. There are several different theories about the causes of food coma and what you can do to prevent the condition from occurring."},{"pid":"de1973080a2d26b1eeb80cb55aebe2f5685596bd","tid":730104,"uid":151430,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-07-05T08:24:32.000Z","msg":"Eating rice makes me sleepy"},{"pid":"f78